        <header>
       <h2>Our Story</h2>
      <p class="10u -1u">
       CLC was founded in 2014 at Northwestern University with the goal of informally connecting students who speak foreign languages.  We have received support from Northwestern’s International Office, Study Abroad Office and Council on Language Instruction.  Within the first three months the program had over 300 participants speaking and learning over 35 different languages.  Founder Kate McCarter won Northwestern University’s Campus Life Award in 2015, which recognizes students who have significantly contributed to the improvement of student life.  We are specifically dedicated to serve academic institutions      
       </p>
